Name: lipoid nephrosis
Definition: A spastic cerebral palsy that affects lower extremities resulting in tight leg and hip muscles. The legs cross at the knees
Synonym: Nephrotic syndrome with lesion of minimal change nephrotic syndrome

Name: familial nephrotic syndrome
Definition: A nephrotic syndrome that has_material_basis_in genetic mutations.

Name: obsolete nephrotic syndrome with lesion of lobular glomerulonephritis
Definition: A nephrotic syndrome that has_material_basis_in genetic mutations.
Synonym: Nephrotic syndrome with Lesion of Lobular Glomerulonephritis

Name: obsolete nephrotic syndrome with lesion of focal glomerulosclerosis
Definition: A nephrotic syndrome that has_material_basis_in genetic mutations.
Synonym: Nephrotic syndrome with Lesion of Focal Glomerulosclerosis
